73class EditorInternalCommand {
74public:
75 bool (*execute)(Frame&, Event*, EditorCommandSource, const String&);
76 bool (*isSupportedFromDOM)(Frame*);
77 bool (*isEnabled)(Frame&, Event*, EditorCommandSource);
78 TriState (*state)(Frame&, Event*);
79 String (*value)(Frame&, Event*);
80 bool isTextInsertion;
81 bool (*allowExecutionWhenDisabled)(Frame&, EditorCommandSource);
82};
83
84typedef HashMap<String, const EditorInternalCommand*, ASCIICaseInsensitiveHash> CommandMap;
85
86static const bool notTextInsertion = false;
87static const bool isTextInsertion = true;

89// Related to Editor::selectionForCommand.
90// Certain operations continue to use the target control's selection even if the event handler
91// already moved the selection outside of the text control.
92static Frame* targetFrame(Frame& frame, Event* event)
93{
94 if (!event)
95 return &frame;
96 if (!is<Node>(event->target()))
97 return &frame;
98 return downcast<Node>(*event->target()).document().frame();
99}
100
101static bool applyCommandToFrame(Frame& frame, EditorCommandSource source, EditAction action, Ref<EditingStyle>&& style)
102{
103 // FIXME: We don't call shouldApplyStyle when the source is DOM; is there a good reason for that?
104 switch (source) {
105 case CommandFromMenuOrKeyBinding:
106 // Use InvertColor for testing purposes. foreColor and backColor are never triggered with CommandFromMenuOrKeyBinding outside DRT/WTR.
107 frame.editor().applyStyleToSelection(WTFMove(style), action, Editor::ColorFilterMode::InvertColor);
108 return true;
109 case CommandFromDOM:
110 case CommandFromDOMWithUserInterface:
111 frame.editor().applyStyle(WTFMove(style), EditAction::Unspecified, Editor::ColorFilterMode::UseOriginalColor);
112 return true;
113 }
114 ASSERT_NOT_REACHED();
115 return false;
116}
117
118static bool isStylePresent(Editor& editor, CSSPropertyID propertyID, const char* onValue)
119{
120 // Style is considered present when
121 // Mac: present at the beginning of selection
122 // Windows: present throughout the selection
123 if (editor.behavior().shouldToggleStyleBasedOnStartOfSelection())
124 return editor.selectionStartHasStyle(propertyID, onValue);
125 return editor.selectionHasStyle(propertyID, onValue) == TriState::True;
126}
127
128static bool executeApplyStyle(Frame& frame, EditorCommandSource source, EditAction action, CSSPropertyID propertyID, const String& propertyValue)
129{
130 return applyCommandToFrame(frame, source, action, EditingStyle::create(propertyID, propertyValue));
131}
132
133static bool executeApplyStyle(Frame& frame, EditorCommandSource source, EditAction action, CSSPropertyID propertyID, CSSValueID propertyValue)
134{
135 return applyCommandToFrame(frame, source, action, EditingStyle::create(propertyID, propertyValue));
136}
137
138static bool executeToggleStyle(Frame& frame, EditorCommandSource source, EditAction action, CSSPropertyID propertyID, const char* offValue, const char* onValue)
139{
140 bool styleIsPresent = isStylePresent(frame.editor(), propertyID, onValue);
141 return applyCommandToFrame(frame, source, action, EditingStyle::create(propertyID, styleIsPresent ? offValue : onValue));
142}
143
144static bool executeApplyParagraphStyle(Frame& frame, EditorCommandSource source, EditAction action, CSSPropertyID propertyID, const String& propertyValue)
145{
146 auto style = MutableStyleProperties::create();
147 style->setProperty(propertyID, propertyValue);
148 // FIXME: We don't call shouldApplyStyle when the source is DOM; is there a good reason for that?
149 switch (source) {
150 case CommandFromMenuOrKeyBinding:
151 frame.editor().applyParagraphStyleToSelection(style.ptr(), action);
152 return true;
153 case CommandFromDOM:
154 case CommandFromDOMWithUserInterface:
155 frame.editor().applyParagraphStyle(style.ptr());
156 return true;
157 }
158 ASSERT_NOT_REACHED();
159 return false;
160}

162static bool executeInsertFragment(Frame& frame, Ref<DocumentFragment>&& fragment)
163{
164 ASSERT(frame.document());
165 ReplaceSelectionCommand::create(*frame.document(), WTFMove(fragment), ReplaceSelectionCommand::PreventNesting, EditAction::Insert)->apply();
166 return true;
167}
168
169static bool executeInsertNode(Frame& frame, Ref<Node>&& content)
170{
171 auto fragment = DocumentFragment::create(*frame.document());
172 if (fragment->appendChild(content).hasException())
173 return false;
174 return executeInsertFragment(frame, WTFMove(fragment));
175}
176
177static bool expandSelectionToGranularity(Frame& frame, TextGranularity granularity)
178{
179 VisibleSelection selection = frame.selection().selection();
180 auto oldRange = selection.toNormalizedRange();
181 selection.expandUsingGranularity(granularity);
182 auto newRange = selection.toNormalizedRange();
183 if (!newRange || newRange->collapsed())
184 return false;
185 auto affinity = selection.affinity();
186 if (!frame.editor().client()->shouldChangeSelectedRange(*oldRange, *newRange, affinity, false))
187 return false;
188 frame.selection().setSelectedRange(*newRange, affinity, FrameSelection::ShouldCloseTyping::Yes);
189 // FIXME: Why do we ignore the return value from setSelectedRange here?
190 return true;
191}
192
193static TriState stateStyle(Frame& frame, CSSPropertyID propertyID, const char* desiredValue)
194{
195 if (frame.editor().behavior().shouldToggleStyleBasedOnStartOfSelection())
196 return frame.editor().selectionStartHasStyle(propertyID, desiredValue) ? TriState::True : TriState::False;
197 return frame.editor().selectionHasStyle(propertyID, desiredValue);
198}
199
200static String valueStyle(Frame& frame, CSSPropertyID propertyID)
201{
202 // FIXME: Rather than retrieving the style at the start of the current selection,
203 // we should retrieve the style present throughout the selection for non-Mac platforms.
204 return frame.editor().selectionStartCSSPropertyValue(propertyID);
205}
206
207static TriState stateTextWritingDirection(Frame& frame, WritingDirection direction)
208{
209 bool hasNestedOrMultipleEmbeddings;
210 WritingDirection selectionDirection = EditingStyle::textDirectionForSelection(frame.selection().selection(),
211 frame.selection().typingStyle(), hasNestedOrMultipleEmbeddings);
212 // FXIME: We should be returning TriState::Indeterminate when selectionDirection == direction && hasNestedOrMultipleEmbeddings
213 return (selectionDirection == direction && !hasNestedOrMultipleEmbeddings) ? TriState::True : TriState::False;
214}
215
216static unsigned verticalScrollDistance(Frame& frame)
217{
218 Element* focusedElement = frame.document()->focusedElement();
219 if (!focusedElement)
220 return 0;
221 auto* renderer = focusedElement->renderer();
222 if (!is<RenderBox>(renderer))
223 return 0;
224 const RenderStyle& style = renderer->style();
225 if (!(style.overflowY() == Overflow::Scroll || style.overflowY() == Overflow::Auto || focusedElement->hasEditableStyle()))
226 return 0;
227 int height = std::min<int>(downcast<RenderBox>(*renderer).clientHeight(), frame.view()->visibleHeight());
228 return static_cast<unsigned>(Scrollbar::pageStep(height));
229}

244static bool executeCreateLink(Frame& frame, Event*, EditorCommandSource, const String& value)
245{
246 // FIXME: If userInterface is true, we should display a dialog box to let the user enter a URL.
247 if (value.isEmpty())
248 return false;
249 ASSERT(frame.document());
250 CreateLinkCommand::create(*frame.document(), value)->apply();
251 return true;
252}

254static bool executeCut(Frame& frame, Event*, EditorCommandSource source, const String&)
255{
256 if (source == CommandFromMenuOrKeyBinding) {
257 UserTypingGestureIndicator typingGestureIndicator(frame);
258 frame.editor().cut(Editor::FromMenuOrKeyBinding::Yes);
259 } else
260 frame.editor().cut();
261 return true;
262}

267 return true;

270static bool executeDefaultParagraphSeparator(Frame& frame, Event*, EditorCommandSource, const String& value)
271{
272 if (equalLettersIgnoringASCIICase(value, "div"))
273 frame.editor().setDefaultParagraphSeparator(EditorParagraphSeparatorIsDiv);
274 else if (equalLettersIgnoringASCIICase(value, "p"))
275 frame.editor().setDefaultParagraphSeparator(EditorParagraphSeparatorIsP);
276
277 return true;
278}
279
280static bool executeDelete(Frame& frame, Event*, EditorCommandSource source, const String&)
281{
282 switch (source) {
283 case CommandFromMenuOrKeyBinding: {
284 // Doesn't modify the text if the current selection isn't a range.
285 UserTypingGestureIndicator typingGestureIndicator(frame);
286 frame.editor().performDelete();
287 return true;
288 }
289 case CommandFromDOM:
290 case CommandFromDOMWithUserInterface:
291 // If the current selection is a caret, delete the preceding character. IE performs forwardDelete, but we currently side with Firefox.
292 // Doesn't scroll to make the selection visible, or modify the kill ring (this time, siding with IE, not Firefox).
293 TypingCommand::deleteKeyPressed(*frame.document(), frame.editor().shouldSmartDelete() ? TypingCommand::SmartDelete : 0);
294 return true;
295 }
296 ASSERT_NOT_REACHED();
297 return false;
298}

331static bool executeDeleteToEndOfLine(Frame& frame, Event*, EditorCommandSource, const String&)
332{
333 // Despite its name, this command should delete the newline at the end of
334 // a paragraph if you are at the end of a paragraph (like DeleteToEndOfParagraph).
335 frame.editor().deleteWithDirection(SelectionDirection::Forward, TextGranularity::LineBoundary, true, false);
336 return true;
337}

339static bool executeDeleteToEndOfParagraph(Frame& frame, Event*, EditorCommandSource, const String&)
340{
341 // Despite its name, this command should delete the newline at the end of
342 // a paragraph if you are at the end of a paragraph.
343 frame.editor().deleteWithDirection(SelectionDirection::Forward, TextGranularity::ParagraphBoundary, true, false);
344 return true;
345}

347static bool executeDeleteToMark(Frame& frame, Event*, EditorCommandSource, const String&)
348{
349 auto& editor = frame.editor();
350 auto& selection = frame.selection();
351 auto markRange = editor.mark().toNormalizedRange();
352 auto selectionRange = selection.selection().toNormalizedRange();
353 if (markRange && selectionRange) {
354 if (!selection.setSelectedRange(unionRange(*markRange, *selectionRange), Affinity::Downstream, FrameSelection::ShouldCloseTyping::Yes))
355 return false;
356 }
357 editor.performDelete();
358 editor.setMark(selection.selection());
359 return true;
360}

402static bool executeFormatBlock(Frame& frame, Event*, EditorCommandSource, const String& value)
403{
404 String tagName = value.convertToASCIILowercase();
405 if (tagName[0] == '<' && tagName[tagName.length() - 1] == '>')
406 tagName = tagName.substring(1, tagName.length() - 2);
407
408 auto qualifiedTagName = Document::parseQualifiedName(xhtmlNamespaceURI, tagName);
409 if (qualifiedTagName.hasException())
410 return false;
411
412 ASSERT(frame.document());
413 auto command = FormatBlockCommand::create(*frame.document(), qualifiedTagName.releaseReturnValue());
414 command->apply();
415 return command->didApply();
416}
417
418static bool executeForwardDelete(Frame& frame, Event*, EditorCommandSource source, const String&)
419{
420 switch (source) {
421 case CommandFromMenuOrKeyBinding:
422 frame.editor().deleteWithDirection(SelectionDirection::Forward, TextGranularity::CharacterGranularity, false, true);
423 return true;
424 case CommandFromDOM:
425 case CommandFromDOMWithUserInterface:
426 // Doesn't scroll to make the selection visible, or modify the kill ring.
427 // ForwardDelete is not implemented in IE or Firefox, so this behavior is only needed for
428 // backward compatibility with ourselves, and for consistency with Delete.
429 TypingCommand::forwardDeleteKeyPressed(*frame.document());
430 return true;
431 }
432 ASSERT_NOT_REACHED();
433 return false;
434}

476static bool executeInsertLineBreak(Frame& frame, Event* event, EditorCommandSource source, const String&)
477{
478 switch (source) {
479 case CommandFromMenuOrKeyBinding:
480 return targetFrame(frame, event)->eventHandler().handleTextInputEvent("\n"_s, event, TextEventInputLineBreak);
481 case CommandFromDOM:
482 case CommandFromDOMWithUserInterface:
483 // Doesn't scroll to make the selection visible, or modify the kill ring.
484 // InsertLineBreak is not implemented in IE or Firefox, so this behavior is only needed for
485 // backward compatibility with ourselves, and for consistency with other commands.
486 TypingCommand::insertLineBreak(*frame.document(), 0);
487 return true;
488 }
489 ASSERT_NOT_REACHED();
490 return false;
491}

493static bool executeInsertNewline(Frame& frame, Event* event, EditorCommandSource, const String&)
494{
495 Frame* targetFrame = WebCore::targetFrame(frame, event);
496 return targetFrame->eventHandler().handleTextInputEvent("\n"_s, event, targetFrame->editor().canEditRichly() ? TextEventInputKeyboard : TextEventInputLineBreak);
497}

641
642static bool executeMovePageDown(Frame& frame, Event*, EditorCommandSource, const String&)
643{
644 unsigned distance = verticalScrollDistance(frame);
645 if (!distance)
646 return false;
647 return frame.selection().modify(FrameSelection::AlterationMove, distance, FrameSelection::DirectionDown,
648 UserTriggered, FrameSelection::AlignCursorOnScrollAlways);
649}
650
651static bool executeMovePageDownAndModifySelection(Frame& frame, Event*, EditorCommandSource, const String&)
652{
653 unsigned distance = verticalScrollDistance(frame);
654 if (!distance)
655 return false;
656 return frame.selection().modify(FrameSelection::AlterationExtend, distance, FrameSelection::DirectionDown,
657 UserTriggered, FrameSelection::AlignCursorOnScrollAlways);
658}

905 return true;
906}

1040static bool executeSelectToMark(Frame& frame, Event*, EditorCommandSource, const String&)
1041{
1042 auto& editor = frame.editor();
1043 auto& selection = frame.selection();
1044 auto markRange = editor.mark().toNormalizedRange();
1045 auto selectionRange = selection.selection().toNormalizedRange();
1046 if (!markRange || !selectionRange) {
1047 SystemSoundManager::singleton().systemBeep();
1048 return false;
1049 }
1050 selection.setSelectedRange(unionRange(*markRange, *selectionRange), Affinity::Downstream, FrameSelection::ShouldCloseTyping::Yes);
1051 // FIXME: Why do we ignore the return value from setSelectedRange here?
1052 return true;
1053}

1100static bool executeSwapWithMark(Frame& frame, Event*, EditorCommandSource, const String&)
1101{
1102 RefPtr<Document> protection(frame.document());
1103 Ref<Frame> protector(frame);
1104 const VisibleSelection& mark = frame.editor().mark();
1105 const VisibleSelection& selection = frame.selection().selection();
1106 if (mark.isNone() || selection.isNone()) {
1107 SystemSoundManager::singleton().systemBeep();
1108 return false;
1109 }
1110 frame.selection().setSelection(mark);
1111 frame.editor().setMark(selection);
1112 return true;
1113}

1199static bool defaultValueForSupportedCopyCut(Frame& frame)
1200{
1201 auto& settings = frame.settings();
1202 if (settings.javaScriptCanAccessClipboard())
1203 return true;
1204
1205 switch (settings.clipboardAccessPolicy()) {
1206 case ClipboardAccessPolicy::Allow:
1207 case ClipboardAccessPolicy::RequiresUserGesture:
1208 return true;
1209 case ClipboardAccessPolicy::Deny:
1210 return false;
1211 }
1212
1213 ASSERT_NOT_REACHED();
1214 return false;
1215}
1216
1217static bool supportedCopyCut(Frame* frame)
1218{
1219 if (!frame)
1220 return false;
1221
1222 bool defaultValue = defaultValueForSupportedCopyCut(*frame);
1223
1224 EditorClient* client = frame->editor().client();
1225 return client ? client->canCopyCut(frame, defaultValue) : defaultValue;
1226}
1227
1228static bool defaultValueForSupportedPaste(Frame& frame)
1229{
1230 auto& settings = frame.settings();
1231 if (settings.javaScriptCanAccessClipboard() && settings.domPasteAllowed())
1232 return true;
1233
1234 return settings.domPasteAccessRequestsEnabled();
1235}
1236
1237static bool supportedPaste(Frame* frame)
1238{
1239 if (!frame)
1240 return false;
1241
1242 bool defaultValue = defaultValueForSupportedPaste(*frame);
1243
1244 EditorClient* client = frame->editor().client();
1245 return client ? client->canPaste(frame, defaultValue) : defaultValue;
1246}

1255static bool enabledVisibleSelection(Frame& frame, Event* event, EditorCommandSource)
1256{
1257 // The term "visible" here includes a caret in editable text or a range in any text.
1258 const VisibleSelection& selection = frame.editor().selectionForCommand(event);
1259 return (selection.isCaret() && selection.isContentEditable()) || selection.isRange();
1260}
1261
1262static bool caretBrowsingEnabled(Frame& frame)
1263{
1264 return frame.settings().caretBrowsingEnabled();
1265}
1266
1267static EditorCommandSource dummyEditorCommandSource = static_cast<EditorCommandSource>(0);
1268
1269static bool enabledVisibleSelectionOrCaretBrowsing(Frame& frame, Event* event, EditorCommandSource)
1270{
1271 // The EditorCommandSource parameter is unused in enabledVisibleSelection, so just pass a dummy variable
1272 return caretBrowsingEnabled(frame) || enabledVisibleSelection(frame, event, dummyEditorCommandSource);
1273}
1274
1275static bool enabledVisibleSelectionAndMark(Frame& frame, Event* event, EditorCommandSource)
1276{
1277 const VisibleSelection& selection = frame.editor().selectionForCommand(event);
1278 return ((selection.isCaret() && selection.isContentEditable()) || selection.isRange())
1279 && frame.editor().mark().isCaretOrRange();
1280}
1281
1282static bool enableCaretInEditableText(Frame& frame, Event* event, EditorCommandSource)
1283{
1284 const VisibleSelection& selection = frame.editor().selectionForCommand(event);
1285 return selection.isCaret() && selection.isContentEditable();
1286}
1287
1288static bool allowCopyCutFromDOM(Frame& frame)
1289{
1290 auto& settings = frame.settings();
1291 if (settings.javaScriptCanAccessClipboard())
1292 return true;
1293
1294 switch (settings.clipboardAccessPolicy()) {
1295 case ClipboardAccessPolicy::Allow:
1296 return true;
1297 case ClipboardAccessPolicy::Deny:
1298 return false;
1299 case ClipboardAccessPolicy::RequiresUserGesture:
1300 return UserGestureIndicator::processingUserGesture();
1301 }
1302
1303 ASSERT_NOT_REACHED();
1304 return false;
1305}
1306
1307static bool enabledCopy(Frame& frame, Event*, EditorCommandSource source)
1308{
1309 switch (source) {
1310 case CommandFromMenuOrKeyBinding:
1311 return frame.editor().canDHTMLCopy() || frame.editor().canCopy();
1312 case CommandFromDOM:
1313 case CommandFromDOMWithUserInterface:
1314 return allowCopyCutFromDOM(frame) && (frame.editor().canDHTMLCopy() || frame.editor().canCopy());
1315 }
1316 ASSERT_NOT_REACHED();
1317 return false;
1318}
1319
1320static bool enabledCut(Frame& frame, Event*, EditorCommandSource source)
1321{
1322 switch (source) {
1323 case CommandFromMenuOrKeyBinding:
1324 return frame.editor().canDHTMLCut() || frame.editor().canCut();
1325 case CommandFromDOM:
1326 case CommandFromDOMWithUserInterface:
1327 return allowCopyCutFromDOM(frame) && (frame.editor().canDHTMLCut() || frame.editor().canCut());
1328 }
1329 ASSERT_NOT_REACHED();
1330 return false;
1331}
1332
1333static bool enabledClearText(Frame& frame, Event*, EditorCommandSource)
1334{
1335 UNUSED_PARAM(frame);
1336 return false;
1337}
1338
1339static bool enabledInEditableText(Frame& frame, Event* event, EditorCommandSource)
1340{
1341 return frame.editor().selectionForCommand(event).rootEditableElement();
1342}
1343
1344static bool enabledDelete(Frame& frame, Event* event, EditorCommandSource source)
1345{
1346 switch (source) {
1347 case CommandFromMenuOrKeyBinding:
1348 return frame.editor().canDelete();
1349 case CommandFromDOM:
1350 case CommandFromDOMWithUserInterface:
1351 // "Delete" from DOM is like delete/backspace keypress, affects selected range if non-empty,
1352 // otherwise removes a character
1353 return enabledInEditableText(frame, event, source);
1354 }
1355 ASSERT_NOT_REACHED();
1356 return false;
1357}
1358
1359static bool enabledInEditableTextOrCaretBrowsing(Frame& frame, Event* event, EditorCommandSource)
1360{
1361 // The EditorCommandSource parameter is unused in enabledInEditableText, so just pass a dummy variable
1362 return caretBrowsingEnabled(frame) || enabledInEditableText(frame, event, dummyEditorCommandSource);
1363}
1364
1365static bool enabledInRichlyEditableText(Frame& frame, Event*, EditorCommandSource)
1366{
1367 const VisibleSelection& selection = frame.selection().selection();
1368 return selection.isCaretOrRange() && selection.isContentRichlyEditable() && selection.rootEditableElement();
1369}
1370
1371static bool allowPasteFromDOM(Frame& frame)
1372{
1373 auto& settings = frame.settings();
1374 if (settings.javaScriptCanAccessClipboard() && settings.domPasteAllowed())
1375 return true;
1376
1377 return settings.domPasteAccessRequestsEnabled() && UserGestureIndicator::processingUserGesture();
1378}
1379
1380static bool enabledPaste(Frame& frame, Event*, EditorCommandSource source)
1381{
1382 switch (source) {
1383 case CommandFromMenuOrKeyBinding:
1384 return frame.editor().canDHTMLPaste() || frame.editor().canPaste();
1385 case CommandFromDOM:
1386 case CommandFromDOMWithUserInterface:
1387 return allowPasteFromDOM(frame) && (frame.editor().canDHTMLPaste() || frame.editor().canPaste());
1388 }
1389 ASSERT_NOT_REACHED();
1390 return false;
1391}
1392
1393static bool enabledRangeInEditableText(Frame& frame, Event*, EditorCommandSource)
1394{
1395 return frame.selection().isRange() && frame.selection().selection().isContentEditable();
1396}
1397
1398static bool enabledRangeInRichlyEditableText(Frame& frame, Event*, EditorCommandSource)
1399{
1400 return frame.selection().isRange() && frame.selection().selection().isContentRichlyEditable();
1401}
1402
1403static bool enabledRedo(Frame& frame, Event*, EditorCommandSource)
1404{
1405 return frame.editor().canRedo();
1406}

1553
1554static String valueFormatBlock(Frame& frame, Event*)
1555{
1556 const VisibleSelection& selection = frame.selection().selection();
1557 if (selection.isNoneOrOrphaned() || !selection.isContentEditable())
1558 return emptyString();
1559 auto* formatBlockElement = FormatBlockCommand::elementForFormatBlockCommand(selection.firstRange());
1560 if (!formatBlockElement)
1561 return emptyString();
1562 return formatBlockElement->localName();
1563}

1565// allowExecutionWhenDisabled functions
1566
1567static bool allowExecutionWhenDisabled(Frame&, EditorCommandSource)
1568{
1569 return true;
1570}
1571
1572static bool doNotAllowExecutionWhenDisabled(Frame&, EditorCommandSource)
1573{
1574 return false;
1575}
1576
1577static bool allowExecutionWhenDisabledCopyCut(Frame&, EditorCommandSource source)
1578{
1579 switch (source) {
1580 case CommandFromMenuOrKeyBinding:
1581 return true;
1582 case CommandFromDOM:
1583 case CommandFromDOMWithUserInterface:
1584 return false;
1585 }
1586
1587 ASSERT_NOT_REACHED();
1588 return false;
1589}
1590
1591static bool allowExecutionWhenDisabledPaste(Frame& frame, EditorCommandSource)
1592{
1593 if (frame.mainFrame().loader().shouldSuppressTextInputFromEditing())
1594 return false;
1595 return true;
1596}

1758 // These unsupported commands are listed here since they appear in the Microsoft
1759 // documentation used as the starting point for our DOM executeCommand support.
1760 //
1761 // 2D-Position (not supported)
1762 // AbsolutePosition (not supported)
1763 // BlockDirLTR (not supported)
1764 // BlockDirRTL (not supported)
1765 // BrowseMode (not supported)
1766 // ClearAuthenticationCache (not supported)
1767 // CreateBookmark (not supported)
1768 // DirLTR (not supported)
1769 // DirRTL (not supported)
1770 // EditMode (not supported)
1771 // InlineDirLTR (not supported)
1772 // InlineDirRTL (not supported)
1773 // InsertButton (not supported)
1774 // InsertFieldSet (not supported)
1775 // InsertIFrame (not supported)
1776 // InsertInputButton (not supported)
1777 // InsertInputCheckbox (not supported)
1778 // InsertInputFileUpload (not supported)
1779 // InsertInputHidden (not supported)
1780 // InsertInputImage (not supported)
1781 // InsertInputPassword (not supported)
1782 // InsertInputRadio (not supported)
1783 // InsertInputReset (not supported)
1784 // InsertInputSubmit (not supported)
1785 // InsertInputText (not supported)
1786 // InsertMarquee (not supported)
1787 // InsertSelectDropDown (not supported)
1788 // InsertSelectListBox (not supported)
1789 // InsertTextArea (not supported)
1790 // LiveResize (not supported)
1791 // MultipleSelection (not supported)
1792 // Open (not supported)
1793 // PlayImage (not supported)
1794 // Refresh (not supported)
1795 // RemoveParaFormat (not supported)
1796 // SaveAs (not supported)
1797 // SizeToControl (not supported)
1798 // SizeToControlHeight (not supported)
1799 // SizeToControlWidth (not supported)
1800 // Stop (not supported)
1801 // StopImage (not supported)
1802 // Unbookmark (not supported)
1803
1804 CommandMap& commandMap = *new CommandMap;
1805
1806 for (auto& command : commands) {
1807 ASSERT(!commandMap.get(command.name));
1808 commandMap.set(command.name, &command.command);
1809 }
1810
1811 return commandMap;
1812}
1813
1814static const EditorInternalCommand* internalCommand(const String& commandName)
1815{
1816 static const CommandMap& commandMap = createCommandMap();
1817 return commandName.isEmpty() ? 0 : commandMap.get(commandName);
1818}
1819
1820Editor::Command Editor::command(const String& commandName)
1821{
1822 return Command(internalCommand(commandName), CommandFromMenuOrKeyBinding, m_document);
1823}
1824
1825Editor::Command Editor::command(const String& commandName, EditorCommandSource source)
1826{
1827 return Command(internalCommand(commandName), source, m_document);
1828}
1829
1830bool Editor::commandIsSupportedFromMenuOrKeyBinding(const String& commandName)
1831{
1832 return internalCommand(commandName);
1833}
1834
1835Editor::Command::Command()
1836{
1837}
1838
1839Editor::Command::Command(const EditorInternalCommand* command, EditorCommandSource source, Document& document)
1840 : m_command(command)
1841 , m_source(source)
1842 , m_document(command ? &document : nullptr)
1843 , m_frame(command ? document.frame() : nullptr)
1844{
1845 ASSERT(command || !m_document);
1846}
1847
1848bool Editor::Command::execute(const String& parameter, Event* triggeringEvent) const
1849{
1850 if (!isEnabled(triggeringEvent)) {
1851 // Let certain commands be executed when performed explicitly even if they are disabled.
1852 if (!allowExecutionWhenDisabled())
1853 return false;
1854 }
1855
1856 m_document->updateLayoutIgnorePendingStylesheets();
1857 if (m_document->frame() != m_frame)
1858 return false;
1859
1860 return m_command->execute(*m_frame, triggeringEvent, m_source, parameter);
1861}
1862
1863bool Editor::Command::execute(Event* triggeringEvent) const
1864{
1865 return execute(String(), triggeringEvent);
1866}
1867
1868bool Editor::Command::isSupported() const
1869{
1870 if (!m_command)
1871 return false;
1872 switch (m_source) {
1873 case CommandFromMenuOrKeyBinding:
1874 return true;
1875 case CommandFromDOM:
1876 case CommandFromDOMWithUserInterface:
1877 return m_command->isSupportedFromDOM(m_frame.get());
1878 }
1879 ASSERT_NOT_REACHED();
1880 return false;
1881}
1882
1883bool Editor::Command::isEnabled(Event* triggeringEvent) const
1884{
1885 if (!isSupported() || !m_frame)
1886 return false;
1887 return m_command->isEnabled(*m_frame, triggeringEvent, m_source);
1888}
1889
1890TriState Editor::Command::state(Event* triggeringEvent) const
1891{
1892 if (!isSupported() || !m_frame)
1893 return TriState::False;
1894 return m_command->state(*m_frame, triggeringEvent);
1895}
1896
1897String Editor::Command::value(Event* triggeringEvent) const
1898{
1899 if (!isSupported() || !m_frame)
1900 return String();
1901 if (m_command->value == valueNull && m_command->state != stateNone)
1902 return m_command->state(*m_frame, triggeringEvent) == TriState::True ? "true"_s : "false"_s;
1903 return m_command->value(*m_frame, triggeringEvent);
1904}
1905
1906bool Editor::Command::isTextInsertion() const
1907{
1908 return m_command && m_command->isTextInsertion;
1909}
1910
1911bool Editor::Command::allowExecutionWhenDisabled() const
1912{
1913 if (!isSupported() || !m_frame)
1914 return false;
1915 return m_command->allowExecutionWhenDisabled(*m_frame, m_source);
1916}
